{"title": "Good Words: 1870", "description": "Good Words was an English monthly magazine directed at evangelicals and nonconformists, particularly of the lower middle classes. It contained overtly religious material as well as serialized novels, dialogues, articles on science and art, essays, sketches of travel, and poetry. The content was chosen with an eye to ensuring that the devout could read it on Sundays without sin.\r\nIn 1870, Good Words ran three serialized novels: <i>Carlino</i>, <i>Dorothy Fox</i>, and <i>Fernyhurst Court</i>. The magazine also ran several series of travel sketches: <i>Days in North India</i> by Norman Macleod, <i>A Visit to the Country of Vaudois</i> by S. Smiles, <i>Letters from the Tropics</i> by C. Kingsley, and <i>Wanderings in the Desert of the Exodus</i> by E.H. Palmer. - Summary by Elsie Selwyn\r\n", "duration": 25085, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "18443", "name": "Norman Macleod"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/goodwords1870_2508_librivox/good_words_1870_2508.jpg", "copyright_year": "1870", "genres": ["Literary Collections"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Elsie Selwyn"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Annise"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Elijah Fisher"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Carlino, Chapter 1", "readers": [11169], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/goodwords1870_2508_librivox/goodwordsjan1870_01_macleod_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1766}, {"section": 2, "title": "Carlino, Chapter 2", "readers": [11169], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/goodwords1870_2508_librivox/goodwordsjan1870_02_macleod_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2421}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Air-Mothers by Charles Kinsley", "readers": [8425], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/goodwords1870_2508_librivox/goodwordsjan1870_03_macleod_64kb.mp3", "duration": 527}, {"section": 4, "title": "Days in North India by Norman Macleod,